  "prompt": "How does a non-US citizen/resident  search for jobs in US?",
  "response": "Here are several strategies for non-US citizens/residents to search for jobs in the US:\n\n1. Visa Options\n- H-1B work visa\n- TN visa (for Canadian/Mexican professionals)\n- L-1 intracompany transfer visa\n- Optional Practical Training (OPT) for international students\n- J-1 exchange visitor programs\n\n2. Job Search Platforms\n- LinkedIn\n- Indeed\n- Glassdoor\n- Monster\n- USJobs.gov (government jobs)\n- Company-specific career websites\n\n3. Networking\n- Professional networking events\n- LinkedIn networking\n- Alumni associations\n- Industry conferences\n- Professional organizations in your field\n\n4. International Job Boards\n- International job sections on major job sites\n- Global recruitment agencies\n- Websites specializing in international job placements\n\n5. Company Sponsorship\n- Look for companies willing to sponsor work visas\n- Target multinational corporations\n- Research companies with history of hiring international talent\n\n6. Additional Strategies\n- Remote work opportunities\n- Internship programs\n- Graduate assistantships\n- Academic research positions\n- Technical skills in high demand fields\n\n7. Legal Considerations\n- Understand visa requirements\n- Consult immigration lawyers\n- Check work authorization regulations\n\nPersistence and targeted approach are key in international job searching.",
